name: BusinessCenterCode
definition: code used to denote a metropolitan area where business is conducted
label: business center code
explanatoryNote: The codes for business centers and municipalities defined herein are largely those identified either as FpML business centers or are locations where there is an exchange, as noted in the ISO 10962 MIC code standard.

name: BusinessDayAdjustmentCode
label: business day adjustment code
definition: code used to denote a convention for specifying what happens when a date falls on a day that is weekend or holiday in some municipality or business center

name: BusinessCenterCodeScheme
definition: coding scheme used to define a set of codes for municipalities or business centers
label: business center code set

name: BusinessCenter
explanatoryNote: Note that business centers, as defined in FpML, are intended for use in specifying the business calendar used by that municipality, or by certain organizations located in that municipality.
